        <abstract> 
<p>His view of <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>.</p> 
            <p>Belief of Duke of Argyll that substituting "variation" and "selection" for creation deifies them.</p>
            <p>Thinks Argyll would accept evolution except for man.</p>
            <p>A’s view of humming-birds.</p>
            <p>Describes discussion with [Victoria,] Princess Royal of Prussia, about evolution.</p> 
<p>New edition of <hi rend="italic">Elements</hi> consistent with <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>.</p> 
        </abstract>
